  "description": "<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p762671/\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_shuangyu.gif\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a><br /><p>\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.yun.hjfile.cn/doc/201601/d9dcd470-3df5-4b6e-b911-41445c099da2_00.jpg\" style=\"line-height: 25.2000007629395px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n\tSpending the winter in Moscow might be bitterly cold (obviously an <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/understatement\" target=\"_blank\">understatement</a>), but it could also be magical &ndash; especially if you see it through the eyes of photographer Kristina Makeeva.<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">在莫斯科过冬可能会把你冻成狗（这里显然是保守说法了），但也可能是魔法般的（奇幻），尤其是如果你通过摄影师</span><span style=\"line-height: 25.2000007629395px;\">Kristina Makeeva</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">的作品看莫斯科。</span></p>\n<p>\n\tGoing around Moscow during Orthodox Christmas, Makeeva was able to capture the city as if it were a winter wonderland. In her photos are locations like Red Square and the Kremlin, both <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/bath\" target=\"_blank\">bathed</a> in snow and colorful lights with people milling about. It&rsquo;s as if you were looking at images straight out of a fairytale!<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">在东正教圣诞节期间，Makeeva在莫斯科徘徊，她镜头下捕捉到的这座城市，宛如一个冬季仙境。其作品里捕捉的场景，比如红场（红场是莫斯科最古老的广场 ，是重大历史事件的见证场所，也是俄罗斯重要节日举行群众集会、大型庆典和阅兵活动的地方，著名旅游景点。是世界上著名的广场之一）和克里姆林宫（克里姆林宫的&ldquo;克里姆林&rdquo;在俄语中意为&ldquo;内城&rdquo;。克里姆林宫享有&ldquo;世界第八奇景&rdquo;的美誉），都聚集着漫无目的的人群，沐浴在漫天纷飞的白雪和流光溢彩的灯光之下。看着这些照片，就仿佛看到了tonghu</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\"></span></p>\n<p>\n\tYou can see more of Kristina Makeeva&rsquo;s photos over on Instagram.<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\"></span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">你可以在</span><span style=\"line-height: 25.2000007629395px;\">Kristina Makeeva</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">的Instagram账号上看到更多的美图。</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\"></span></p>\n<p>\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.y